# Cloudflare Pages headers. Expo copies public/ into dist verbatim.
#
# The HTML + manifest must NEVER be cached: after every deploy the page
# references new hashed bundles, and a cached shell pins users to the previous
# build. `no-cache` (revalidate) was not enough — installed iOS PWAs kept
# serving a stale shell across deploys and glitched until the cache was cleared
# by hand (Tyson, recurring). `no-store` forbids caching the shell outright, so
# every relaunch pulls the current index. The hashed assets stay immutable
# (content-addressed) — the later, more specific rule wins for them.

# no-cache (NOT no-store) since 2026-07-18: a no-store start_url left the
# installed iOS PWA a frozen grey screen — at standalone launch there is no
# stored copy to fall back on and a stalled fetch never retries (beacons show
# Safari booting fine while standalone never executed JS). Freshness is now
# guaranteed by the IN-APP version guard (auto-reload on hash mismatch), so
# revalidation semantics are enough here.
# Scope the rule to the SHELL entry points only. A broad `/*` rule leaks its
# Cache-Control onto the hashed assets too (Cloudflare Pages COMBINES the values
# of every matching rule), and `no-store` there would defeat their immutable
# caching — so target the root, index.html and manifest explicitly instead. The
# PWA launches at `/`, so that is the request that must never be cached.
/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate

/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate

/_expo/static/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
